WEBVTT

00:23.580 --> 00:31.630
<b>Saita no no hana yo</b>

00:23.580 --> 00:31.630
<b>Blooming wildflower</b>

00:31.630 --> 00:39.010
<b>aa douka oshiete o-kure</b>

00:31.630 --> 00:39.010
<b>I beg you, please tell me</b>

00:39.010 --> 00:55.320
<b>Hito wa naze kizutsukeatte arasou no deshou</b>

00:39.010 --> 00:55.320
<b>Why do people fight and hurt each other</b>

00:55.700 --> 01:03.450
<b>Rin to saku hana yo</b>

00:55.700 --> 01:03.450
<b>Valiantly blooming flower</b>

01:03.450 --> 01:10.840
<b>soko kara nani ga mieru</b>

01:03.450 --> 01:10.840
<b>What can you see from your field?</b>

01:10.840 --> 01:27.520
<b>Hito wa naze yurushiau koto dekinai no deshou</b>

01:10.840 --> 01:27.520
<b>Why can't people forgive each other</b>

01:16.010 --> 01:17.340
Have you secured the key?

01:17.760 --> 01:18.590
Yeah.

01:18.590 --> 01:20.510
Good work. I'll guide you out.

01:21.140 --> 01:22.850
We'll meet up in thirty seconds.

01:30.980 --> 01:39.370
<b>Ame ga sugite natsu wa ao o utsushita</b>

01:30.980 --> 01:39.370
<b>The rain passed, and summer took on blue hues</b>

01:39.370 --> 01:46.710
<b>hitotsu ni natte</b>

01:39.370 --> 01:46.710
<b>All alone now</b>

01:47.580 --> 01:55.420
<b>Chiisaku yureta watashi no mae de</b>

01:47.580 --> 01:55.420
<b>You trembled before me</b>

01:55.670 --> 02:03.430
<b>nani mo iwazu ni</b>

01:55.670 --> 02:03.430
<b>Without saying a word</b>

02:19.700 --> 02:26.580
<b>Karete yuku tomo ni</b>

02:19.700 --> 02:26.580
<b>When your friends wilt around you</b>

02:27.580 --> 02:34.670
<b>omae wa nani o omou</b>

02:27.580 --> 02:34.670
<b>What do you think?</b>

02:35.000 --> 02:42.800
<b>Kotoba o motanu sono ha de nanto</b>

02:35.000 --> 02:42.800
<b>With your leaves unable to speak</b>

02:40.180 --> 02:43.930
Please, Fyu-Neru Get this to Gai.

02:42.800 --> 02:51.270
<b>ai o tsutaeru</b>

02:42.800 --> 02:51.270
<b>How do you convey love?</b>

02:55.020 --> 03:03.660
<b>Aa natsu no hi wa kagette kaze ga nabitta</b>

02:55.020 --> 03:03.660
<b>Summer's sun clouded over, the wind streamed by</b>

03:03.370 --> 03:04.530
I'll cover you

03:03.660 --> 03:11.000
<b>futatsu kasanatte</b>

03:03.660 --> 03:11.000
<b>The two overlapped</b>

03:05.370 --> 03:06.990
Now get that to Gai, quick!

03:07.660 --> 03:08.910
Fyu-Neru...

03:11.460 --> 03:19.550
<b>Ikita akashi o watashi wa uta o</b>

03:11.460 --> 03:19.550
<b>I shall sing the proof that you lived</b>

03:16.920 --> 03:17.960
Oh, crap!

03:19.550 --> 03:30.980
<b>na mo naki mono no tame</b>

03:19.550 --> 03:30.980
<b>For the sake of those who have no names</b>

04:04.890 --> 04:06.430
Morning, Shu!

04:06.430 --> 04:08.930
What's the huge yawn for?

04:08.930 --> 04:10.890
Well...

04:10.890 --> 04:12.810
Were you surfing the net or something?

04:13.350 --> 04:15.100
Or playing a game?

04:15.100 --> 04:16.270
Reading?

04:16.560 --> 04:18.570
Something like that, I guess...

04:20.150 --> 04:22.900
Huh. Fine, then.

04:23.900 --> 04:28.160
Danger{...says TerrorAlertUsagi-san, this is srs bsnss}

04:23.900 --> 04:28.160
Danger

04:28.830 --> 04:31.080
Lots of them out today, huh?

04:31.080 --> 04:32.710
Didn't you see the news?

04:32.710 --> 04:35.960
Apparently there was some terrorist attack or something yesterday.

04:35.960 --> 04:39.710
In Odaiba... no, I guess it's called "Ward 24" now.

04:49.430 --> 04:50.560
Hey, Shu!

04:51.270 --> 04:55.560
Oh, sorry, I'm not done with that video for the competition yet.

04:56.400 --> 04:58.310
I didn't come to harp on you about it...

04:58.310 --> 04:59.270
What did you want, then?

05:00.520 --> 05:03.280
I'll get it done by the deadline, don't worry.

05:03.280 --> 05:05.610
Now look, Shu, I—

05:05.610 --> 05:06.950
Let it go, Souta.

05:06.950 --> 05:08.410
He says he can do it, after all.

05:08.410 --> 05:09.870
Okay, we're counting on you!

05:11.870 --> 05:13.790
I feel bad for Souta.

05:13.790 --> 05:18.460
Why? I think I'm trying hard to be socially perceptive here.

05:18.460 --> 05:20.340
You're not succeeding.

05:20.340 --> 05:21.210
Oh...

05:21.210 --> 05:22.460
You're way too dense.

05:22.460 --> 05:23.340
Rise!

05:27.050 --> 05:28.510
<i>I'm dense?</i>

05:29.390 --> 05:32.600
<i>Maybe it's true that my mind works out of step with everyone else's.</i>

05:33.680 --> 05:38.480
<i>It's just that I don't know what to say to other people.</i>

05:39.690 --> 05:42.940
<i>So I hide my nervousness and go along with what they say.</i>

05:42.940 --> 05:45.570
<i>that's how I've made the quasi-friendships in my life.</i>

05:47.110 --> 05:51.160
<i>Right now, Japan operates as a "quasi-independent" nation.</i>

05:51.160 --> 05:52.950
<i>That's what my mom says.</i>

05:53.040 --> 05:56.500
<b>Was a biological Weapon Used!?</b>

05:53.450 --> 05:58.920
<i>Ten years ago, the Apocalypse Virus pandemic wreaked havoc on this country,</i>

05:56.500 --> 05:58.920
<b>Anarchy Reigns</b>

05:59.630 --> 06:03.670
<i>and we relied on an unbelievable amount of help from many other countries.</i>

06:04.340 --> 06:07.220
<i>And we're still dependent on them even now.</i>

06:07.550 --> 06:10.850
<i>Japan's foundations are just barely holding together.</i>

06:13.310 --> 06:15.470
<i>We hear it every day...</i>

06:16.350 --> 06:18.230
<i>"We can't leave this to you."</i>

06:19.350 --> 06:24.070
<i>"You don't have the power to protect the people who are important to you."</i>

06:27.240 --> 06:29.700
<i>But... should we really just accept that?</i>

06:31.030 --> 06:34.660
<i>Isn't there something more that I can do?</i>

06:36.250 --> 06:39.250
<b>Blockade
Zone</b>

06:45.460 --> 06:52.640
<i>Blooming wildflower...</i>

06:53.680 --> 07:00.980
<i>I beg you, please tell me,</i>

07:00.980 --> 07:16.410
<i>Why do people fight and hurt each other?</i>

07:17.580 --> 07:24.880
<i>Valiantly blooming flower...</i>

07:29.510 --> 07:30.220
Wha—

07:32.720 --> 07:35.010
Um, you've got the wrong idea!

07:35.010 --> 07:36.970
I totally didn't want to—

07:37.810 --> 07:38.930
Hey, are you—

07:53.110 --> 07:55.780
It... it's not done yet!

07:55.780 --> 07:57.280
It's a view of my hometown, and—

07:57.280 --> 07:58.040
It's pretty.

08:00.620 --> 08:01.710
Huh?

08:11.630 --> 08:13.760
Um, would you like a rice ball?

08:15.430 --> 08:21.270
London Bridge is falling down, falling down, falling down.

08:21.890 --> 08:27.480
London Bridge is falling down, my fair lady.

08:22.980 --> 08:25.560
Um, you're Inori, aren't you?

08:27.480 --> 08:29.270
The Egoist singer?

08:31.240 --> 08:36.030
<i>London Bridge is falling down, falling down, falling down.</i>

08:36.030 --> 08:38.580
So, what are you doing here?

08:38.580 --> 08:40.950
No, more importantly, why are you so hurt?

08:40.950 --> 08:43.160
We have to get this to Gai.

08:45.460 --> 08:46.380
Take this.

08:47.790 --> 08:50.420
Take this, um...

08:50.420 --> 08:52.510
Shu! Ouma Shu!

08:53.340 --> 08:55.630
You might be able to do it if you try.

08:56.510 --> 08:59.220
But you'll never be able to if you don't.

09:01.100 --> 09:04.140
Ouma Shu... are you a coward?

09:11.440 --> 09:12.230
Huh?

09:14.190 --> 09:16.070
What was that?

09:22.290 --> 09:23.160
Fyu-Neru.

09:25.580 --> 09:26.420
Inori!

09:28.670 --> 09:29.710
Woah there.

09:35.800 --> 09:36.720
You a student?

09:38.090 --> 09:39.510
Y-Yes, Sir!

09:39.510 --> 09:42.720
Um, that girl is hurt. Please don't treat her—

09:42.720 --> 09:44.980
This woman is a criminal.

09:44.980 --> 09:48.770
If you defend her, we'll purge you too, as her accomplice.

09:53.400 --> 09:55.610
What does the data check show?

09:55.610 --> 09:58.860
She's definitely a member of the Funeral Parlor in Rappongi.

10:01.030 --> 10:01.990
Little terrorist scum!

10:05.410 --> 10:06.580
Bring her in.

10:06.580 --> 10:07.370
Yes, Sir!

10:24.470 --> 10:26.390
Should I really just accept this?

10:31.400 --> 10:33.110
Should I really just accept this?

10:36.360 --> 10:42.660
<i>I felt... a little relieved, because I wasn't in danger anymore.</i>

10:43.780 --> 10:45.740
<i>That's how pathetic I am.</i>

10:46.580 --> 10:49.580
<i>When you get right down to it, she was way out of my league.</i>

10:51.330 --> 10:52.130
<i>Take this.</i>

10:54.250 --> 10:55.340
<i>I wanted to take it.</i>

10:58.380 --> 11:01.640
<i>I wanted to get close to her, and touch her hand!</i>

11:04.100 --> 11:08.270
<i>Forget about it, Shu. Rest a while, and you'll be fine.</i>

11:09.560 --> 11:12.650
<i>After that, just go back to your normal self.</i>

11:22.660 --> 11:24.740
<i>We have to get this to Gai.</i>

11:26.240 --> 11:30.500
Seriously? You're telling me to go there?

11:43.760 --> 11:47.430
This might be my last chance to not hate myself.

11:52.850 --> 11:55.150
It had to be here, of all places...

12:01.570 --> 12:05.620
I'm told you've dispatched a squadron to Roppongi.

12:05.620 --> 12:07.620
I believed it was necessary.

12:08.700 --> 12:10.910
That'll provoke unnecessary hostility.

12:10.910 --> 12:13.960
I can't allow it if it's not for an aid mission.

12:13.960 --> 12:15.630
I understand that.

12:15.630 --> 12:21.800
So, just how dangerous is this stolen Void Genome?

12:22.510 --> 12:23.260
That's—

12:23.260 --> 12:26.140
Level 3A classified information.

12:27.220 --> 12:32.310
And so you can't even tell me, GHQ's Supreme Commander?

12:32.980 --> 12:34.390
I'm afraid so, sir.

12:35.270 --> 12:37.020
But please, don't worry.

12:37.020 --> 12:40.780
My Anti Bodies have already apprehended the culprit,

12:40.780 --> 12:43.650
and are searching for the stolen genome as we speak.

12:47.820 --> 12:50.370
Still don't want to talk?

12:52.500 --> 12:57.580
We've been granted the authority to dispose of the diseased without warning.

12:58.630 --> 13:00.750
If you don't tell us where you hid it,

13:00.750 --> 13:05.260
I'll just have to purge every single resident of this neighborhood.

13:12.560 --> 13:14.060
You'll regret this later.

13:17.230 --> 13:18.440
Attention all units.

13:18.900 --> 13:23.190
All residents in our operating area are designated as Stage IV+ infected.

13:23.190 --> 13:25.200
I hereby authorize infection control measures!

13:26.780 --> 13:28.490
What shall we do with the girl?

13:29.070 --> 13:31.990
After we commence hostilities, get rid of her outside.

13:47.720 --> 13:48.970
Is this it?

13:48.970 --> 13:50.010
Hey, you!

13:52.060 --> 13:53.100
Y-Yes?

13:56.230 --> 13:57.440
That thing cook?

13:58.310 --> 13:59.150
Excuse me?

14:00.060 --> 14:01.520
That thing cook rice?

14:02.940 --> 14:07.860
Well, no, I don't <i>think</i> it does...

14:08.410 --> 14:09.530
Leave it.

14:09.530 --> 14:11.580
N-No, I can't do that!

14:13.450 --> 14:16.620
You messin' with me? Just hand it over.

14:17.460 --> 14:19.750
I'm very sorry, but it doesn't belong to me!

14:20.500 --> 14:22.880
She worked so hard to protect this...

14:22.880 --> 14:25.090
So... I'm sorry!

14:37.770 --> 14:40.310
Greetings, my deceased fellows.

14:42.020 --> 14:43.520
"Deceased"?!

14:43.520 --> 14:48.200
Yes. The current situation doesn't allow for your survival.

14:51.620 --> 14:54.580
Therefore, you are all dead.

14:55.200 --> 14:56.950
Don't tell me he's...

14:56.950 --> 14:57.910
...Gai!

14:57.910 --> 14:59.580
You got some balls, kid.

15:14.260 --> 15:16.140
Shit, who is this guy?!

15:37.660 --> 15:38.910
Wait, what?

15:39.500 --> 15:42.290
That's Fyu-Neru, right? Give it back!

15:48.710 --> 15:49.920
You're Ouma Shu?

15:57.140 --> 15:59.430
What about the girl who was with that?

16:03.270 --> 16:05.650
Well... I...

16:06.650 --> 16:07.940
You just abandoned her?

16:19.370 --> 16:23.000
Gai! The GHQ whitecoats are invading!

16:29.590 --> 16:34.090
Damn those bastards! They're firing live rounds at anybody they see!

16:35.970 --> 16:38.720
Tsugumi, what's the word on Ayase and the others?

16:39.100 --> 16:40.310
They're...

16:41.270 --> 16:42.730
Enemy incoming on our left!

16:50.530 --> 16:52.030
Beat it, you're in my way!

16:55.860 --> 16:57.160
Go, Shu!

16:57.160 --> 17:01.290
Don't you dare let go of that thing! Protect it this time!

17:15.260 --> 17:18.760
<i>But... what can I do, exactly?</i>

17:23.430 --> 17:24.520
How many are we up against?

17:25.190 --> 17:27.810
Not sure yet! More keep coming!

17:27.810 --> 17:29.020
Keep it together!

17:34.070 --> 17:35.240
What do you think you're doing?!

18:11.060 --> 18:12.230
Inori!

18:15.820 --> 18:18.410
<i>Do something that's not like you for once, Shu!</i>

18:49.980 --> 18:50.940
What...

18:57.190 --> 18:58.320
What is this?

19:00.410 --> 19:02.870
Shu, please...

19:03.660 --> 19:05.790
...use me.

19:11.330 --> 19:14.420
<i>Take it this time, Shu.</i>

19:15.960 --> 19:17.130
<i>Who...</i>

19:17.130 --> 19:18.920
This is power.

19:19.760 --> 19:24.350
The guilty crown given shape through the bond between hearts.

20:32.460 --> 20:34.290
What... is this?

21:19.760 --> 21:25.770
Mou anata kara aisareru koto mo

21:19.760 --> 21:25.770
These days you love me no more

21:26.390 --> 21:32.400
hitsuyou to sareru koto mo nai

21:26.390 --> 21:32.400
nor am I still treasured by you

21:32.770 --> 21:41.200
Soshite watashi wa koushite hitoribocchi de

21:32.770 --> 21:41.200
Now I am all alone

21:42.990 --> 21:49.080
Ano toki anata wa nante itta no

21:42.990 --> 21:49.080
What did you tell me when we parted?

21:49.710 --> 21:55.710
Todokanai kotoba wa chuu wo mau

21:49.710 --> 21:55.710
The words hung in midair and never reached me

21:56.170 --> 22:02.470
Wakatteru no ni kyou mo shite shimau

21:56.170 --> 22:02.470
I know my dreams and wishes are illusory

22:03.050 --> 22:09.100
kanawanu negaigoto wo

22:03.050 --> 22:09.100
and yet I cannot give up on them

22:12.150 --> 22:19.110
Hanasanaide gyutto te wo nigittete

22:12.150 --> 22:19.110
You said, "Don't let go, hold onto my hand"

22:19.650 --> 22:26.120
anata to futari tsudzuku to itte

22:19.650 --> 22:26.120
and, "We will always be together"

22:26.280 --> 22:34.880
Tsunaida sono te wa atatakakute

22:26.280 --> 22:34.880
Your hands as I held them were warm

22:38.000 --> 22:43.180
yasashikatta

22:38.000 --> 22:43.180
and tender
